claim.claim-text:
1. An adapter with a fuse and an indicator and capable of being used as a plug comprising: 
an upper cover having a shape having two larger ends and a thinner middle portion and being integrally formed by plastics; the upper cover being installed with a fuse inlet hole, an indicator hole and a first notch; the fuse inlet hole being tightly sealed by a first transparent cover; the first transparent cover having a lower block being exactly buckled between the first notch of the upper cover and a groove in the lower cover; when a plug being inserted, the lower block exactly resisting against the transparent cover; the indicator hole being engaged with a second transparent cover; a bottom of the upper cover having a plurality of posts; 
a lower cover having a shape correspondent to the upper cover; the lower cover being installed with a fuse receiving groove, an indicator receiving groove, and a plurality of assembling grooves and a second notch configured with respect to the fuse inlet hole, indicator hole, posts and first notch of the upper cover; a rotary unit receiving groove being formed in front of the fuse receiving groove; left and right sides of the rotary unit receiving groove being connecting piece receiving grooves; two female terminal receiving grooves being extended from the connecting piece receiving grooves, respectively, from the left and right sides of the indicator receiving groove; rear sides of the two female terminal receiving grooves being connected to two receptacle holes, respectively; the indicator receiving groove and the rotary unit receiving groove being installed with an indicator and a cylindrical rotary unit; the buckling grooves at the left and right sides of the cylindrical rotary unit being buckled to two male terminals, respectively, and then the rotary unit being placed in the rotary unit receiving groove; outer lateral surfaces of the two parallel male terminals being buckled with respective connecting pieces; then the two connecting pieces being connected with two female terminals, respectively, thereby, the openings of the two female terminals being exactly connected to respective receptacle holes; a male terminal being connected to the fuse through a connecting piece; by rotating the cylindrical rotary unit, the two male terminals rotating through a predetermined angle so as to be used inconveniently; when the outer plug being inserted into the receptacle holes; since the two female terminals expanding due to the insertion of the plug, the female terminals resisting against a positive and a negative electrode of the indicator; a circuit of the indicator being formed as a loop so as to emit light; 
wherein the indicator has the functions of checking the plug, fuse, circuits of connecting electric devices; furthermore, through the fuse, as current is over tolerance of the fuse, the fuse will melt; as a result, not only the electric devices are protected, but also the firing of electric wire is prevented.

3. An adapter with a fuse and an indicator and capable of using as a plug comprising: 
an upper cover having a shape having two larger ends and a thinner middle portion and being integrally formed by plastics; the upper cover being installed with a fuse inlet hole, an indicator hole and a first notch; the fuse inlet hole being tightly sealed by a first transparent cover; the first transparent cover having a lower block being exactly buckled between the first notch of the upper cover and a groove in the lower cover; when a plug being inserted, it exactly resisting against the transparent cover; the indicator hole being engaged with a second transparent cover; a bottom of the upper cover having a plurality of posts; 
the lower cover having a shape correspondent to the upper cover; the lower cover being installed with a fuse receiving groove, an indicator receiving groove, and a plurality of assembling grooves and a second notch with respect to the fuse inlet hole, indicator hole, posts and first notch of the upper cover; in front of the fuse receiving groove being directly installed with two parallel male terminals and the two male terminals being fixed to fixing positions not to rotate; each male terminal being connected to a connecting piece; each connecting piece being connected to a female terminal; the two female terminals being installed in the female terminal receiving groove and the two female terminals being exactly in contact to the pivotal holes, one of the female terminal being installed to a fuse installed in the fuse receiving groove through a connecting piece; an indicator being installed in the indicator receiving groove, wherein as the adapter being not used, positive and negative terminals of the indicator being not in contact with the two terminals; besides, a bottom of the lower cover being installed with an embedding strip for being embedded into a connecting body; the connecting body having connecting wires and connecting holes which are assembled to remove electric static charges.
